  "inscription": "<br />1 (worn away):  <br />The Upper Burial Ground  <br />Sometimes called Ax's Burial Ground was  <br />[Granted] to the Burrough of Germantown in [1724]  <br />by Paul [Wullf]  <br />[Here are] buried many of the early settlers  and their descendants  <br />[Here are the] graves of Major Irwin, Captain Turner  <br />[Lieutenant] Lucas and six other American soldiers  <br />killed in the Battle of Germantown  <br />The wall was built in 1777  <br />The Site and Relic Society of Germantown 1902  <br />2:  <br />1724  <br />1776  <br />1843  <br />3 (long list of names omitted):  <br />To Honor   <br />the Revolutionary Soldiers Buried Here  <br />Placed by Germantown Chapter Daughters of the American Revolution  <br />1946  <br />4:  <br />In Memory of Soldiers of the War of 1812  <br />Who lie in Upper Germantown Burying Ground  <br />Philadelphia  <br />William Crout, John Paulson  <br />George Knorr, Frederick Sheetz  <br />Jacob K. Knorr, Edward Snyder  <br />Lewis Lehman, Michael Snyder  <br />John Nell, George Streeper  <br />Jeremiah Trout  <br />Placed by Stephen Decatur Chapter  <br />U.S. Daughters of 1812  <br />1945",
